## **1. B (Boron) vs Al (Aluminum)**

**Group 13 – Valence Electrons: 3**

| Aspect            | **Boron (B)**                 | **Aluminum (Al)**                     | **Reason for Differences**                                                                   |
| ----------------- | ----------------------------- | ------------------------------------- | -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| Orbital Number    | 2 energy levels (1s² 2s² 2p¹) | 3 energy levels (1s² 2s² 2p⁶ 3s² 3p¹) | Al has an extra shell → larger atomic radius and lower nuclear attraction on outer electrons |
| Common Oxidation  | +3                            | +3                                    | Same group → same oxidation state; Al⁺³ is more ionic, B⁺³ is more covalent                  |
| Electronegativity | 2.04                          | 1.61                                  | Boron is smaller and pulls electrons more strongly                                           |

